{noformat}
Expression samplerassertions is undefined on line 1, column 6 in template/plugins/buildProcessor/jmeterAggregatorProcessorView.ftl. The problematic instruction: ---------- ==> if samplerassertions.size() > 0 [on line 1, column 1 in template/plugins/buildProcessor/jmeterAggregatorProcessorView.ftl]
{noformat}
looks like jmeter plugin has problems.

I installed Babmoo 2.6.1. It found PHPUnit and added PHPUnit builder correctly without any user action.
However when I created and started a plan using the PHPUnit builder it fails with following error:

{code}
Failed to execute build: Cannot run program "C:\Program Files (x86)\PHP\phpunit" (in directory "C:\Users\Jacek Jaroczynski\bamboo-home\xml-data\build-dir\TEST-TEST"): CreateProcess error=193, %1 is not a valid Win32 application
{code}

The solution was to explicitly configure PHPUnit builder to point at *phpunit.bat* instead of *phpunit*

After upgrading from Bamboo 2.4 to 2.6, the XMPP Notifications we receive started incorrectly reporting 0 tests on successful builds. Example below:

{code}PPRI - TSS Application - Trunk Polling build 165 was SUCCESSFUL (with 0 tests).
http://urltobamboo/bamboo/browse/TSSBUILD-TRUNK-165/{code}

However, the dashboard correctly reports the test count:

{code}Ran: 28 minutes ago   Manual build by Ben Floyd   Duration: 2 minutes   Tests: 718 passed{code}

I cannot figure out what is causing the discrepancy, but it worked prior to the upgrade.
